wikipedia_page.main: Alfred Keeling (14 December 1920 – 1 December 1942) was an English professional footballer who played as a forward.

link_mentions.page: List of footballers killed during World War II
response: * Alfred Keeling – played for Bradford (Park Avenue) (1937–1939). A sergeant in the RAFVR, he was shot down and killed over the Bay of Biscay on 1 December 1942 aged 21.
